  "unmapped_findings": [
    "Fig. 10 tabulates strengthening mechanism contributions to yield strength: M1-SS measured 430 MPa (σ0=350, σG=80), M1-30 measured 860 MPa (σ0=350, σG=90, σS=430), M2-SS measured 660 MPa (σ0=410, σG=100, σOr=120), M2-30 measured 880 MPa (σ0=410, σG=100, σOr=120, σS=220). These tabulated values show minor discrepancies with narrative statements (M2-SS described as ~200 MPa higher than M1-SS; M2-30 stated as 884 MPa).",
    "Fig. 7 presents engineering stress-strain and true stress-strain curves with strain hardening rate curves for M1-SS, M1-30, M2-SS, and M2-30; specific UTS and elongation values for M1-SS and M2-SS are not explicitly stated in the text.",
    "Fig. 11 presents Crussard-Jaoul work-hardening index plots (ln(dσ/dε) vs lnε) showing three stages for M1-SS and two stages for M1-30, whereas M2-SS and M2-30 curves nearly coincide, indicating that the uniform precipitation of κ-carbides reduces work-hardening capacity while Ti/V modification preserves it.",
    "In M1-30, TEM DF imaging revealed a number density of uniformly distributed κ-carbides of approximately 7×10^22 m^-3.",
    "Calculated stacking fault energies are approximately 70 mJ/m^2 for M1 and 78 mJ/m^2 for M2 based on the Olson-Cohen model, indicating dislocation slip as the predominant deformation mode.",
    "The tensile strength increased from 1004 MPa (M1-30) to 1096 MPa (M2-30), but the text does not express this improvement as a percentage.",
    "Fig. 9 schematically illustrates the microstructural evolution in M2 steel: preexisting (Ti,V)C carbides are surrounded by carbon-enriched zones, and upon aging at 550°C κ-carbides preferentially precipitate along the edges of (Ti,V)C carbides."
  ]
